  "texts": [
    "The MLPs were trained to transform CNN-extracted features into phylogenetically informed embeddings.",
    "The architecture employs three separate ResNeXt-101 CNNs, each fine-tuned to analyze different image modalities (wholegrain images, cross-sections, and patches), with the final layers modified to output logit vectors that are then fused into a single probability distribution.",
    "Using these CNN-extracted features to train an MLP that captures phylogenetic relationships through a learned distance function is a core innovation, and enables accurate placement of novel morphotypes within an evolutionary tree.",
    "This requires that morphological features captured by CNNs are fully representative of phylogenetic relationships, which might not hold true for all taxa, and thus misinterpretations in phylogenetic placement remain possible.",
    "In conclusion, this diverse array of studies for classification underscores the transformative impact of DL across various sub-disciplines of paleontology."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}